*retroarch-0.9.9 (07 Jun 2013)
*retroarch-0.9.8-r2 (07 Jun 2013)

  07 Jun 2013; Michał Ziąbkowski <mziab@o2.pl> +retroarch-0.9.8-r2.ebuild,
  +retroarch-0.9.9.ebuild, retroarch-9999.ebuild,
  +files/retroarch-0.9.9-build.patch:
  Bumped. Fixed python flag. Updated deps.

*retroarch-0.9.8-r1 (21 May 2013)

  21 May 2013; Michał Ziąbkowski <mziab@o2.pl> -retroarch-0.9.6-r1.ebuild,
  -retroarch-0.9.7.ebuild, +retroarch-0.9.8-r1.ebuild, retroarch-9999.ebuild,
  -files/retroarch-0.9.6-build.patch, -files/retroarch-0.9.7-build.patch:
  Removed old versions. Removed the dynamic USE flag. Due to the multitude of
  libretro ports available, it makes little sense to have a hard dependency on
  any one of them, so dynamic loading is always on.

*retroarch-0.9.8 (20 Feb 2013)

  20 Feb 2013; Michał Ziąbkowski <mziab@o2.pl> +retroarch-0.9.8.ebuild,
